tasks.result:
### CORRECTION: package.json
```
{
  "name": "nextjs-app",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "private": true,
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "next dev",
    "build": "next build",
    "start": "next start",
    "lint": "next lint"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "next": "14.0.0",
    "react": "18.2.0",
    "react-dom": "18.2.0"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "eslint": "8.50.0",
    "eslint-config-next": "14.0.0"
  }
}
```

### CORRECTION: next.config.js
```
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  reactStrictMode: true,
  swcMinify: true
}

module.exports = nextConfig
```

### LOESUNG fuer package-lock.json:
Die Datei `package-lock.json` muss geloescht und neu generiert werden:

```bash
rm package-lock.json
npm install
```

Dies behebt den JSON-Syntaxfehler in Zeile 1120 (unvollstaendiger String) durch vollstaendige Neugenerierung der Lock-Datei.
